Early Access Review

The good:

-Great art style;
-Great level design;
-Leveling system and upgrades;
-Various pets;
-Various loot drops;
-Nice music;
-4 distinct characters;
-Solo or Co-op;
-Free to play.

The bad:

-Unpolished;
-Unstable frame rate;
-Short campaign;
-Bugs (level medium);
-Connections errors;
-Some mispelled words;
-Some items (like fishes) won't stack;
-The launcher could be improved.


Score: 6/10.
